The paper also discusses computation and maintenance strategies, which are related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions factorization width, which is a concept from computational complexity theory, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the time needed to update the query result, which is related to artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses trade-offs, which is a common theme in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
